[586.183183, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@972cf0f30065:/app# "]
[592.567105, "i", "sed -n '1,220p' /app/docs/api_contract.md\n"]
[592.567529, "o", "sed -n '1,220p' /app/docs/api_contract.md"]
[592.567653, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[592.56972, "o", "This document is the normative REST contract for the notes API. Automated checks use arbitrary title and content strings in requests; only the behaviors, status codes, headers, and JSON field names here matter.\r\n\r\nStore notes in /app/data/notes.db. Read the shared secret from /app/config/api.key and trim surrounding whitespace before comparing it to the X-API-Key header on mutating requests. The stock api.key file ships with tb3_notes_api_secret_2026. POST, PUT, and DELETE require a matching key or the server responds unauthorized. GET never requires the key; a bad or missing key on a mutating call is unauthorized.\r\n\r\nEvery JSON response must use a JSON content type and include an access-control header that allows any origin. OPTIONS preflight must advertise GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and OPTIONS, and must allow Content-Type and X-API-Key as request headers. Preflight may return empty or non-empty success.\r\n\r\n"]
[592.569869, "o", "POST /api/notes accepts JSON with string title and content. Title must be present and non-empty; an empty object or missing or blank title is a client error. Success is HTTP 201 with a body containing numeric id plus stored title and content. GET /api/notes returns a JSON array of objects with id, title, and content. Optional limit and offset query parameters are integers: default limit 50, maximum 100, default offset 0. /api/notes?limit=100 returns at most one hundred rows; /api/notes?limit=999 is capped the same way. The total row count before paging goes in the X-Total-Count header.\r\n\r\nGET /api/notes/{id} returns that object. A missing id returns HTTP 404 with JSON {\"error\":\"not found\"} using that exact lowercase message string, including for ids such as /api/notes/99999 on GET, PUT, or DELETE. PUT uses the same field rules as POST, returns HTTP 200 with saved fields when the row exists, or the same not-found JSON when it does not. Successful DELETE returns HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\":\"deleted\"}; deleting a missing id returns the same not-found JSON as GET. Reject POST or PUT bodies larger than 65536 bytes with HTTP 413 and a JSON error body.\r\n\r\nSQLite access must remain correct under concurrent requests. Verifiers may reset /app/data/notes.db and send bursts of about fifteen parallel POST requests; every stored row must still appear in responses afterward.\r\n"]
